div.div:
Casual style:
- You'll want a minimum set of equipment to participate in all kinds of modes from time to time
- Cash and other resources might be scarce
Minimum Card Set:
- Slime of any color
- 1x Super Silver of any element
- Any % for equipment 2nd skill will do
- Would be better if you're able to prioritize weapons' gold force
Minimim PVP Set:
- Water Set of Magic, Sword, Boots
- Boots prefer Accel. Boots 6s / Invisible 3s as their 2nd skill
Minimum PVE Set:
- Water Axe, preferably Max Damage
- Fire Set of Magic, Staff, Boots, Pendant
- Boots prefer Accel. Boots 4~6s as their 2nd skill
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Semi-hardcore style:
- You'll want more variations and better stats in weapons to gain better performance
- Better, if not the best, resource rates becomes a basic requirement
- To enhance stat improvement, you might want to chip in with Premium Subscriptions & bundles
Advanced Set, on top of Minimum Set:
- Snow Man
- Super Silvers of 2+ elements
- Gold forces on as many cards as possible
Advanced PVP Set:
- Anything you feel comfortable when DCS calls for Cards other than water or swords
Advanced PVE Set:
- Crit Leo (lion with a Korea flag headband, not to be confused with Judge Leo)
- Water/Earth bow, preferably Max Time Down & Triple Shot
- Fire Set of Magic, Axe, Boots
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Hardcore style:
- You'll find yourself looking into intense PVP sessions
- You'll be striving to collect as many daily resource available as possible
Hardcore Set, on top of Advanced Set:
- Penguin (if you're into Magic attacks)
- Super Silvers of all 4 elements
- E Super Silvers, best if they match the elements of your most frequently used sets
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Extra-hardcore style:
- I guess you could figure out what you're looking for?
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Things other than vanilla gameplay:
Freebies
- One set of untradable cards for every account, can be used only once
- Pick an element to get a quick start
- Lobby Chat command: @freebies set water
- Lobby Chat command: @freebies set fire
- Lobby Chat command: @freebies set earth
- Lobby Chat command: @freebies set wind
DMS (Daily Mission System)
- The basic stuff for everyone to gain cash and other random stuff
- Most server events involves extra goodies upon clearing DMS
- Kill monsters in Quests / land KOs on PVP opponents / First-time clears of Boss Raids
- Lobby chat command: @dms
- Hourly, daily and weekly objectives & rewards
DCS (Daily Challenge System)
- Was meant to be a daily stuff, now (patch v333) changed to hourly
- Buff resource rate by playing with maps, modes. characters & equipment specified
- Lobby chat command: @dcs
- One refresh chance is available each hour
GEN coin:
- not to be confused with cryptocurrencies outside this server
- In-game currency to buy stuff
- Various sources
- Lobby Chat command: @gc-info
X-GEN coin:
- not to be confused with cryptocurrencies outside this server
- In-game currency to buy stuff
- Donation exclusive
- Lobby Chat command: @gc-info
MRC (Micro Credits)
- In-game currency to buy stuff
- Various sources with the major one being Boss Raid
- Lobby Chat command: @mrc
Loot Crates:
- Random but very important items
- Lobby Chat command: @lootcrate
Ultra Crates:
- A bit better than Loot Crates
- Lobby Chat command: @lootcrate
Code Shop:
- Consumables available in Code
- Lobby Chat command: @codeshop
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Modes to play (patch v333):
PVE
- Quests
- Mission Impossible 300
- Boss Raid (variant of Mission)
PVP, resource oriented
- Team Play
- Assault
- Survival
- King Survival
- Crystal Capture
- Event PVP Modes (random modifiers, available on Wednesdays and Sundays)
PVP, guild war oriented
- Tournament
- Fight Club
Enjoy Modes
- Soccer
- Dodge
